  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About the Project</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    PoliSoNI stands for <strong>Poli</strong>tical <strong>So</strong>cial <strong>N</strong>etwork
    in <strong>I</strong>ndonesia.
    <br></br>
    <p>This project is supported by <a href = "https://www.universiteitleiden.nl/en/humanities/centre-for-digital-humanities" style="color :steelblue">
    Leiden University Centre for Digital Humanities</a> and is a part of the 
    <a href = "https://lu-human.github.io/" style="color :steelblue">
    Leiden Humanities AI and NLP group</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">The complex network</div>
    Having a wide and early access to knowledge, people and resources is extremely important in attaining political goals, especially for aspiring politicians who want to enter the political arena. In PoliSoNI, we will use network science to understand how social (e.g., familial ties) and political ties (e.g., incumbent party members) may impact electability, and at the same time reveal the underlying patterns, topologies, connections and communities in the large-scale socio-political network.
  </div>

